enhanced_by.reason: The isValid method relies on the initialization of the RegexValidator object with a set of regular expressions.
This constructor initializes the RegexValidator with a single regular expression and case sensitivity, which is relevant for setting up the test environment.
The match method also validates a value against the set of regular expressions and returns matched groups, which can inform the construction of assertions for the isValid method.
The validate method aggregates matched groups into a String, which can be used to create more complex assertions for the isValid method.
